100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 9, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing disarmament and the ongoing tensions in Europe post-World War I. In the United States, the controversial trial of the Scopes "Monkey" case continued to spark national debate over evolution and education. Meanwhile, in Britain, the government faced pressure over its handling of a nationwide coal strike, threatening to disrupt the economy.
